almost time for wine i got through my supermarket trip earlier  just   i decided rather than walking to our local one as i have done for 6 weeks  i would take my car to a bigger one to have more choice and be able to get more but it was awful  it was pretty quick to get in but once i was inside  it was way too busy which made it impossible to keep apart from the supermarket staff let alone the other people  i actually felt very anxious to be around so many people and i spent a fortune  i wont be doing that again but at least we will be very well stocked for a while  i even treated myself to these flowers   this afternoon i managed to move the ladders on the bunk beds by myself  with actual tools and stuff  so the room is finally finished  the star wars sheets arrived too so they have been washed and tumbled  ready for using tonight  the sheets are pretty bright and not very insta friendly but my boys really love them and that is the important thing  this afternoon we are hunkered down watching a film  it has been a long week but happy that we are all happy  safe and well  i hope you are too  periodhomesofinsta riponhouselife oldtownliving victorianhouselife victorianhome periodproperty realperiodhome periodstyle periodliving flowers quarantine weekend

have you ever felt like your heart has been on god’s surgical table and moreso now   where it seems like your thoughts and emotions have finally caught up with you    • • have you found it easy to avoid the worries  the hurts  the pains  the wounds  the bruises of your heart  through the busyness of life   but that escape place of “busyness” doesn’t seem to be at bay now and you’re finally confronted with the rawness of your heart with nowhere to hide   and it seems each day god is surfacing the compiled and hidden things you never wanted to admit to or face as you knew the pain would be too much to face • • what of if god told you  you’re in safe hands; his hands   and what you thought didn’t matter  but caused great hurt  worry  anxiety  grief and defence to your heart  is actually what he cares about most  more than the ‘works of your hands’   and he wants to have a time of openness and intimacy to discuss these things with you • • what of if the things you thought he didn’t care about are actually the things he cares most about  allow him in  • • it’s okay - he wants to stabilise the heart beat of your heart - to give you his true peace  the surgery may hurt  but it will lead to desired healing and wholeness  • • he’s got you just where he wants you allow him in  ❤️ • •  meditation hesgotyou quarantine quarantime heartsurgery pain hurt grief relief wholeness peace acceptance inspired  pensketch judahelart

the sourdough chronicles  cont’d : teo happy loaves of marinated olive country bread with herbs de province and toasted sesame seeds      made two loaves that baked beautifully this little noe starter is truly a gift that keeps on giving       we initially added only half the required amount of water to the leaven  and i thought it would be a mess  fortunately  hubs then added water  based on feel and texture of the dough   which resulted in a drier but easier to handle dough baby  with each bulk fermentation  the dough became more firm and airy  but not as hydrated and sticky as the previous bakes   end result: delicious  full  airy and soft sourdough with crackling  crunchy exteriors  have to work on timing next time  so we aren’t up until 10 pm      happy mother’s day
